 sudo apt install **ttttmmmmm***

creat session => **ttttmmmmm*** new -s mysession

kill session => **ttttmmmmm*** kill-session -t mysession

Ctrl-b s          Choose a session from the sessions list

 ctrl+b t show the time

 ctrl+b " to add awindow

ctrl+b [  or ]

ctrl+b z to zoom page

ctrl+b , to rename session

**ttttmmmmm*** a -t mysession  to open a session

############ Step 1 – Install Node.js

First of all, you need to install node.js on your system. Use the following set of commands to add node.js PPA in your Ubuntu system and install it.

sudo apt-get install python-software-properties

curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_12.x | sudo -E bash -

sudo apt-get install nodejs

node --version
npm --version

Step 2 – Install Angular/CLI

npm install -g @angular/cli
ng --version

ng new hello-angular4

cd hello-angular4
ng serve

ng serve --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080
